<h1>Augmented Reality: Models</h1>
<h2>Floorplan</h2>
<p>
  To measure my apartment dimensions I relied on old-fashioned techniques (tape measurer) and innovative computer 
  vision software. In terms of the new technology, I utilized the iOS application <a href="https://www.magicplan.app/">Magicplan</a>
  to construct a 2D and 3D models of my living space. Using the measurements provided by the models, I crafted 3D models of my apartment
  to virtually render wall studs in my iOS ARKit application.
</p>
<center>
  <%= image_tag "ArriveFloorplan.png", :class => "style_image", :size => "450x300" %>
</center>
<center>Apartment Floorplan</center>
<h2>Magicplan</h2>
<p>
  The Magicplan software provided a simple and intuitive application to measure my apartment and create 3D models. Using computer vision in the context 
  of object recognition, Magicplan allows a user to measure a living space by walking around the space and aligning the camera with the room's features. 
  Once finished, Magicplan outputs a 2D floorplan and 3D model of the space, highlighting the dimensions and prominent features in the room.
</p>
