<h2>SceneKit</h2>
<p>
  In addition to generating models with proprietary software, I also experimented with designing 3D models from within Xcode's
  <a href="https://developer.apple.com/documentation/scenekit/">SceneKit Editor</a>. The SceneKit Editor not only easily imported 
  external models (.obj), converting to the relevant file extension when necessary (.scn), but also offered the tools necessary to 
  design and export custom 3D models. The two figures below demonstrate a model imported into SceneKit from Autodesk and another 
  designed from scratch from within the application.
</p>
